   <title>
    The 38-kDa Hop homologue is ubiquitously expressed in
    <em>
     C. elegans
    </em>
   </title>
   <p>
    The observation of a TPR1-depleted Hop protein raises questions about the functionality of the gene product. Therefore, we were interested in analyzing the expression of the Hop homologue of
    <em>
     C. elegans
    </em>
    . A polyclonal antibody was generated against recombinant CeHop and was used to determine the size of the expressed protein in
    <em>
     C. elegans
    </em>
    extracts. The translated CeHop was detectable at the predicted size in wildtype nematodes under normal growth conditions (
    <a>
     Fig. 2
    </a>
    a) and matched the size of the recombinant protein. Thus, CeHop is expressed constitutively and deletion of TPR1 is observable also at the protein level, excluding any major posttranscriptional or posttranslational modifications of the gene product.
   </p>
