    <a>
     Fig. 2
    </a>
    f,
    <a>
     Table 2
    </a>
    ). Additionally,
    <em>
     hsf-1(sy441)
    </em>
    /
    <em>
     R09E12.3(RNAi)
    </em>
    developed endomitotic oocytes in the uterus (
    <a>
     Fig. 2
    </a>
    e, arrows). Despite the endomitotic oocytes and the drastically shortened distal gonad arms, other features of the gonad were found to be in place. Development of oocytes emanating from the distal gonad arm showed the characteristic pattern of six bivalent chromosomes distal to the spermatheca (
    <a>
     Fig. 2
    </a>
    h). Sperm-filled spermathecae were observed in some nematodes, although many
    <em>
     hsf-1(sy441)
    </em>
    /
    <em>
